description: For sale: $259,900. Sturgeon Lake home! Truly a nice find at a great price with awesome views of the lake! Step out from here to the large upper deck to enjoy the sites and sounds of the loons on the lake. 3 nice sized bedrooms and full bath are also on this main level! The walkout basement is ready to be finished to double your space- foundation is poured concrete insulated walls! Newer bath with walk in shower on lower level. description:
Recently sold: $525,000. ZILLOW PRICE: The Zillow estimated property value is 410, 330.  I understand that this Zillow price is determined by the assessed county taxes.  I understand that the reason for the lower assessed county taxes is that the home is a double dome construction  and hence requires a special buyer.   This home was build by a cement contractor for himself and his family.  I met the contractor in 2004, a year after he had lost the home to the bank.  The contractor told me that he had spent 1.2 million in building the home in the late 90's, without counting the cost of the 121 acres and his labor as the builder.  This cost can easily be observed in an inspection of the home.

SPECIAL FEATURES: Built as a bed and breakfast in 1997, but used as a single family residence since 2004.  9 bedrooms and 7 bathrooms.  Realtor has previously estimated size of home as 10,000 sq. feet on 3 levels.  Built like a fortress by a cement contractor for his own personal use. Racquetball court, large laundry, large sauna, jacuzzi, large sun room/greenhouse on upper deck.  In ground heat, wood stoves, propane heaters provide versatile and redundant heat sources in this large but energy efficient home.  121 acres with 1 1/2 miles of beautiful trails.  3+ car age,  large fenced garden area with raised beds and fruit trees, lots of shed space for extra storage.  Scenic land, panoramic views and large pond. An outdoor hand pump for water and a very large quantity of seasoned oak firewood that is available to the new owner gives a hint of self-sufficiency to the prospective buyer. Most of the rooms are furnished with handcrafted furniture worth many thousands of dollars which are available to the new owner.  About 6 miles from Moose Lake, MN.  Seller reserves right to change terms of sale to allow opportunity for relocation.  Visits to property by appointment only.

description: Recently sold: $350,000. Absolutely stunning SE view of Sturgeon lake! This unique property offers 230 ft of awesome lake frontage & sits on about 0.7 ac. You'll notice pride of ownership everywhere! 3 bedroom rambler built in 1970 with addition in 1997. It has full bathroom plus half bath. Open floor plan, big Marvin windows with greatest view of the lake, beautiful hardwood floor in the kitchen/living rm, large family room also facing the lake. Master bedroom has His/Hers closets. Main floor washer/dryer. Lower level offers a 3rd smaller bedroom, workshop area, utility & more storage space. Finished sq ft is about 1360. Outside you'll have 10x16 shed + another shed, aggregate overlook with steps, another maintenance free deck, lake side deck, firepit paved area. The absolutely great feature is the electrical LIFT that takes you down to the lake and up smoothly! Previous owners paid about 30k for it. Property is very well maintained! Home has forced air and electric heat + AC, wood stove is in the living room, roof new in 2017, new rain gutter in 2018. L-shape aluminum dock. Septic is compliant (two 1500 gallons holding tanks), drilled well. Property is located about 7 min from the Sturgeon lake exit.     In addition you also have an OPTION for buy another over 3 acre parcel across the road with 36x60 Lester pole shed/garage with electric and two doors with gravel floor. Asking price $85,000. Contact agent for more information. Set up your showing today!

description: Recently sold: $293,000. Sturgeon lake at it's finest! 100 ft of awesome lake frontage with Rip Rap shoreline and sand bottom. Property has dream water frontage with a few comfy steps down to the lakeshore, perfect elevation & privacy. Come take a look!

description: Recently sold: $299,000. Beautiful modern home built new in 2015, consisting of "top of the line" finishes: Custom cabinetry, custom tile showers, granite countertops, tile backsplashes, all tile on the main level of the house(really feels good with the in-floor heat). description: Recently sold: $250,000. Rare find! Here is a great property on Sturgeon Lake with level sandy lake frontage! 221 ft of a Riprap shore line. Beautiful West exposure with wonderful lake views! Traditional style solid home with vinyl siding and 3 bedrooms, 3/4 bathroom. Open floor plan! Good size kitchen w/breakfast bar. Wood burning Fire place, excellent quality big Anderson windows! Main floor bedroom has His & Hers closets and it's facing the lake. Upstairs you will have 2 more bedrooms with nice balcony + unreal lake views. Main floor laundry, Propane boiler with hot water baseboards. There is 2 car 28x24 detached garage, guest house 24x24 +10x16 storage area and 8x18 screened porch. It has a kitchenette and half bath and sleeping area upstairs. Ton of potential! Property has a big lot about 0.8 ac and has a drilled well and a private septic/holding tank. You will have a lot of room to play and run around and possibly you'll be able to build another garage/shed. Sturgeon lake is about 1700 acres and it's an excellent lake for fishing and recreational activity. Located only about 1,5 hr from Twin Cities.
